# Whitelist: only the files the Dockerfile actually COPYs feed the
# build. Keeps the context small and prevents new top-level files
# (helm values, k8s manifests, docs, tests) from silently bloating it.
*
!scripts
!scripts/**
!ui
!ui/**
!server.py
!metrics.py
!Dockerfile
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.log
**/*.swp
**/WindowsServer/
values-*.yaml
.env
.env.*
